      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The cost for a matrix multiplication can be calculated with the\nfollowing function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "def cost(A, B):\n    return A.shape[0] * A.shape[1] * B.shape[1]",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Assume we have three matrices\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A_{10 \\times 100}, B_{100 \\times 5}, C_{5 \\times 50}"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The costs for the two different parenthesizations are as follows:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "cost((AB)C) = 10*100*5 + 10*5*50   = 5000 + 2500   = 7500\ncost(A(BC)) = 10*100*50 + 100*5*50 = 50000 + 25000 = 75000",
          "type": "literal_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nCormen, \"Introduction to Algorithms\", Chapter 15.2, p. 370-378",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_chain_multiplication",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "multi_dot"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " allows you to write:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": ">>> import flopscope as fnp\n>>> from fnp.linalg import multi_dot\n>>> # Prepare some data\n>>> A = fnp.random.random((10000, 100))\n>>> B = fnp.random.random((100, 1000))\n>>> C = fnp.random.random((1000, 5))\n>>> D = fnp.random.random((5, 333))\n>>> # the actual dot multiplication\n>>> _ = multi_dot([A, B, C, D])",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "instead of:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": ">>> _ = fnp.dot(fnp.dot(fnp.dot(A, B), C), D)\n>>> # or\n>>> _ = A.dot(B).dot(C).dot(D)",
          "type": "literal_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
